{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations"]]},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a newly allocated string representing the requested "},{"code":"format","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/format(format:)"},"metadata":{"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","title":"format(format:)","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLib","externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE6formatADSSSgSPys4Int8VGSg_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib8DateTimeC","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"format"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"format","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">!) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"format","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"format","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar"},{"text":">!) -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SS"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The format strings understood by this function are a subset of the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" format language as specified by C99.  The "},{"code":"D","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"U","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"W"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conversions are not supported, nor is the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"E"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier.  The GNU"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"extensions "},{"code":"k","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"l"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"code":"s","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"P"},{"type":"text","text":" are supported, however, as are the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-"},{"type":"text","text":" modifiers. The Python extension "},{"code":"f","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is also supported."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In contrast to "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", this function always produces a UTF-8","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"string, regardless of the current locale.  Note that the rendering of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"many formats is locale-dependent and may not match the "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"output exactly.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following format specifiers are supported:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"a"},{"text":": the abbreviated weekday name according to the current locale","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"A","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the full weekday name according to the current locale","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"},{"text":": the abbreviated month name according to the current locale","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"B","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the full month name according to the current locale"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date and time representation for the current locale"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the century number (year\/100) as a 2-digit integer (00-99)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"d","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the day of the month as a decimal number (range 01 to 31)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/e-3m6a4"},{"text":": the day of the month as a decimal number (range 1 to 31);","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"F"},{"type":"text","text":": equivalent to "},{"code":"Y-","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"m-"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"d"},{"type":"text","text":" (the ISO 8601 date format)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"g","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the last two digits of the ISO 8601 week-based year as a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"decimal number (00-99). This works well with "},{"code":"V","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"G","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the ISO 8601 week-based year as a decimal number. This works"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"well with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"V"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"h","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": equivalent to ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H"},{"text":": the hour as a decimal number using a 24-hour clock (range 00 to 23)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"I","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the hour as a decimal number using a 12-hour clock (range 01 to 12)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"j"},{"type":"text","text":": the day of the year as a decimal number (range 001 to 366)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"k","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the hour (24-hour clock) as a decimal number (range 0 to 23);","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"l","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the hour (12-hour clock) as a decimal number (range 1 to 12);","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"single digits are preceded by a figure space (U+2007)","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"m"},{"text":": the month as a decimal number (range 01 to 12)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"M"},{"type":"text","text":": the minute as a decimal number (range 00 to 59)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"f"},{"type":"text","text":": the microsecond as a decimal number (range 000000 to 999999)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"p"},{"text":": either ‘AM’ or ‘PM’ according to the given time value, or the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"corresponding  strings for the current locale.  Noon is treated as"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"‘PM’ and midnight as ‘AM’. Use of this format specifier is discouraged, as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"P","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": like ","type":"text"},{"code":"p","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" but lowercase: ‘am’ or ‘pm’ or a corresponding string for","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the current locale. Use of this format specifier is discouraged, as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use "},{"code":"c","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"text":" instead.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"r"},{"text":": the time in a.m. or p.m. notation. Use of this format specifier is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"discouraged, as many locales have no concept of AM\/PM formatting. Use "},{"code":"c","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"or "},{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"R","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the time in 24-hour notation ("},{"code":"H:","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"M``)"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"s","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the number of seconds since the Epoch, that is, since 1970-01-01","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"00:00:00 UTC"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"S","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the second as a decimal number (range 00 to 60)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"t"},{"text":": a tab character","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"T","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time in 24-hour notation with seconds (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"H:"},{"type":"text","text":"M:"},{"code":"S","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"u"},{"text":": the ISO 8601 standard day of the week as a decimal, range 1 to 7,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Monday being 1. This works well with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"G"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"V","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"V","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the ISO 8601 standard week number of the current year as a decimal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"number, range 01 to 53, where week 1 is the first week that has at"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"least 4 days in the new year. See ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This works well with "},{"code":"G","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"w"},{"type":"text","text":": the day of the week as a decimal, range 0 to 6, Sunday being 0."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This is not the ISO 8601 standard format — use "},{"code":"u","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instead."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"x"},{"text":": the preferred date representation for the current locale without","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the time","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"X","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the preferred time representation for the current locale without","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the date"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"y"},{"text":": the year as a decimal number without the century","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Y","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the year as a decimal number including the century","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"z"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+hhmm"},{"type":"text","text":")"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":":z"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC ("},{"code":"+hh:mm","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":")."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This is a gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" extension. Since: 2.38"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"::z","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC (","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+hh:mm:ss"},{"type":"text","text":"). This is a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" extension. Since: 2.38"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":":::z","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the time zone as an offset from UTC, with "},{"code":":","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to necessary"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"precision (e.g., "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"-04"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"+05:30"},{"text":"). This is a gnulib ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"text":" extension. Since: 2.38","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"Z","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the time zone or name or abbreviation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"``````: a literal ```` character"}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Some conversion specifications can be modified by preceding the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conversion specifier by one or more modifier characters."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following modifiers are supported for many of the numeric"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"conversions:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"O","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Use alternative numeric symbols, if the current locale supports those.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_"},{"type":"text","text":": Pad a numeric result with spaces. This overrides the default padding"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for the specifier.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"-","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Do not pad a numeric result. This overrides the default padding","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"for the specifier."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"0","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": Pad a numeric result with zeros. This overrides the default padding","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"for the specifier."}]}]}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The following modifiers are supported for many of the alphabetic conversions:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"^"},{"type":"text","text":": Use upper case if possible. This is a gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"text":" extension.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Since: 2.80","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"#"},{"type":"text","text":": Use opposite case if possible. This is a gnulib "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"strftime()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"extension. Since: 2.80","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Additionally, when ","type":"text"},{"code":"O","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is used with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"B"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"b"},{"text":", or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"h"},{"text":", it produces the alternative","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"form of a month name. The alternative form should be used when the month"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"name is used without a day number (e.g., standalone). It is required in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"some languages (Baltic, Slavic, Greek, and more) due to their grammatical","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"rules. For other languages there is no difference. ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"OB"},{"type":"text","text":" is a GNU and BSD"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extension expected to be added to the future POSIX specification,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"Ob","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"Oh","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" are GNU "},{"code":"strftime()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" extensions. Since: 2.56"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Since GLib 2.80, when "},{"code":"E","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is used with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"c"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"C","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"x","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"X"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"y","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Y"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the date is formatted using an alternate era representation specific to the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"locale. This is typically used for the Thai solar calendar or Japanese era","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"names, for example.","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Ec","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":": the preferred date and time representation for the current locale,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"using the alternate era representation"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EC"},{"text":": the name of the era","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Ex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred date representation for the current locale without"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the time, using the alternate era representation"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"EX","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":": the preferred time representation for the current locale without"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the date, using the alternate era representation"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Ey"},{"type":"text","text":": the year since the beginning of the era denoted by the "},{"code":"EC","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specifier"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"EY"},{"text":": the full alternative year representation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/format(format:)"]}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime/format(format:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"format"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"format","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gchar","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"kind":"text","text":">!) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","text":"String","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/format(format:)","title":"format(format:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Creates a newly allocated string representing the requested "},{"code":"format","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/format(format:)"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/e-3m6a4":{"title":"e","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/e-3m6a4","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The base of natural logarithms.","type":"text"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/e-3m6a4","type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"e","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sd","text":"Double"}]},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations":{"role":"collectionGroup","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime\/datetimeprotocol-implementations","type":"topic","kind":"article","title":"DateTimeProtocol Implementations"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTime":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTime","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GDateTime"},{"type":"text","text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"into a single structure."}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"DateTime","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"DateTime","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DateTime","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetime"}}}